          'InfoMuslimtxtShow': [
            "\n\nSincerity:\n\nAllah Almighty said:\n\n(And they were not commanded except to worship Allah, [being] sincere to Him in religion, inclining to truth, and to establish prayer and to give zakah. And that is the correct religion.)\n\nAl-Bayyinah: 5\n",
            "\n\nPure repentance to Allah\n\nThe Messenger of Allah ﷺ said:\n\nWhoever repents before the sun rises from its west, Allah will accept his repentance.\n\nNarrated by Muslim 2703\n",
            "\n\nIndeed, Allah Almighty accepts the repentance of a servant as long as he has not reached the throes of death.\n\nNarrated by Tirmidhi (3537)\nand authenticated by Al-Albani\n",
            "\n\nUmrah:\n\nThe Prophet ﷺ said:\n\nPerforming Umrah in Ramadan is equivalent to a Hajj, or a Hajj with me.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari and Muslim\n",
            "\n\nReciting and reading the Quran:\n\nRecite the Quran, for it will come as an intercessor for its reciters on the Day of Resurrection.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nLearning and teaching the Quran:\n\n(The best among you are those who learn the Quran and teach it.)\n\nNarrated by Bukhari\n",
            "\n\nRemembering Allah Almighty:\n\nShall I not inform you of the best of your deeds,\nthe purest of them with your Master,\nthe highest of them in rank,\nand better for you than spending gold and silver,\nand better for you than meeting your enemy\nand striking their necks and them striking your necks?\n\nThey said: Yes.\n\nHe said: The remembrance of Allah Almighty.\n\nNarrated by Tirmidhi\n",
            "\n\nPerfecting the ablution:\n\nWhoever performs ablution and perfects it, his sins depart from his body, even from beneath his nails.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nThe testimony after ablution:\n\nWhoever performs ablution and perfects it,\n\nthen says:\n\nI bear witness that there is no deity except Allah, and I bear witness that Muhammad is His servant and His Messenger.\n\nO Allah, make me among those who repent and make me among those who purify themselves.\n\nThe gates of Paradise are opened for him to enter through whichever he wishes.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nMaintaining ablution:\n\nRemain steadfast, and you will not count [all the good deeds], and know that the best of your deeds is prayer, and none maintains ablution except a believer.\n\nNarrated by Ibn Majah\n",
            "\n\nUsing the siwak:\n\nWere it not that I might overburden my ummah, I would have commanded them to use the siwak at every prayer.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari and Muslim\n",
            "\n\nPraying two rak'ahs after ablution:\n\nWhoever performs ablution and perfects it,\n\nand then prays two rak'ahs focusing on them with his heart and face,\n\nParadise becomes obligatory for him.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nSupplication after the call to prayer:\n\nWhoever says when he hears the call to prayer:\n\nO Allah, Lord of this perfect call and established prayer, grant Muhammad the intercession and favor, and raise him to the praiseworthy position You have promised him,\n\nmy intercession will be granted for him on the Day of Resurrection.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari\n",
            "\n\nSupplication between the call to prayer and the commencement:\n\nThe supplication between the call to prayer and the commencement is not rejected.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari\n",
            "\n\nMaintaining the five daily prayers:\n\nWhenever a Muslim performs a prescribed prayer,\n\nperfecting its ablution, humility, and bowing,\n\nit becomes an expiation for all his past sins, as long as he does not commit a major sin, and this is for all time.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nMaintaining the prayer at its prescribed time:\n\nThe Messenger of Allah ﷺ was asked:\n\nWhich deed is the best?\n\nHe said: Prayer at its prescribed time.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari and Muslim\n",
            "\n\nMaintaining the Fajr and Asr prayers:\n\nWhoever prays the two cool prayers (Fajr and Asr) will enter Paradise.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari\n",
            "\n\nMaintaining the Friday prayer:\n\nThe five daily prayers,\nand from one Friday prayer to the next,\nand from one Ramadan to the next,\nare expiations for whatever sins come in between, so long as one avoids major sins.\n\nNarrated by Muslim\n",
            "\n\nSeeking the hour of response on Friday:\n\nThere is a time on Friday during which a Muslim, if he prays and asks Allah for something, will be granted what he asked for.\n\nNarrated by Bukhari and Muslim\n",
            "\n\nReciting Surah Al-Kahf on Friday:\n\nWhoever recites Surah Al-Kahf on Friday will have a light shine for him between two Fridays.\n\nNarrated by Nasa'i and Al-Hakim\nand authenticated by Sheikh Al-Albani\nin Sahih Al-Jami'\n"
